result.execSummary:
The defendant Edward L Murphy III was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Failure to Support Child (120 Days+), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(2).
  • Failure to Support Child (<120 Days), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(3).
  • Failure to Support Child (<120 Days), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(3).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Edward L Murphy III in court with attorney Jeanne Lila Zamzow.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Hendee states that this is a motion to terminate the DPA based on the defendant did not remain current or pay current child support.  Atty Zamzow states that the defendant is not contesting the motion to terminate. 

BY THE COURT:  Court grants the motion to terminate the DPA; finds the defendant guilty of Ct. 1.  

Atty Hendee is prepared to proceed with sentencing.  Atty Hendee waives the request for as PSI.
Atty Zamzow is prepared to proceed today; waives request for PSI.

BY THE COURT:  PSI waived from both counsel.

Atty Hendee makes sentencing recommendations.  Atty Hendee asks to provide the CS amount to the court at a later date.
Atty Zamzow makes sentencing arguments.

BY THE COURT:  Withhold Sentence; 24 month Probation with conditions:
30 days in the Marquette County Jail w/huber; conditional time (Report date will be determined by the Agent)
Pay Child Support Owed (Atty Hendee will have 5 days to submit the current amount due)
Comply with all child support payments
Maintain full-time employment or conduct the 5 job searches as CSA requests
If child support order is modifed; the required payments that is ordered will be modified.
Court Costs = $268.00
DNA Sample + $250.00 Surcharge
  
If probation is discharged/revoked with outstanding financial obligations due, a civil judgment shall be entered for the balance due and/or other collection procedures will be implemented. If revoked and sent to prison, DOC shall withhold 25% of all inmate monies to pay fines/costs/surcharges/restitution with the balance due as a condition of extended supervision/parole.

  **Court advises defendant that they have been convicted of a Felony and advises rights of voting privileges and of owning a firearm.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Edward L Murphy III in court with attorney Jeanne L. Zamzow.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Hendee states there is a resolution to this case.  State moves to amend Cts 2-3 to Misd. Failure to Support, contrary to 948.22(3).  There will be a 36 month DPA on Ct 1 and probation on Cts 2-3.  Atty Zamzow agrees.  Defendant waives his right to preliminary hearing.  Court questions Atty Zamzow.  Court questions defendant as to the waiver.  BY THE COURT:  Court accepts defendants waiver and finds it to be made freely, voluntarily and intelligently.  BY THE COURT:  Court finds probable cause that a felony was committed and this defendant committed it.  Case bound over for trial or further proceedings.
State files Information.  Atty Zamzow received the Information and waives it's reading.    Recess.   Court in session.
Defendant enters No Contest plea to Ct 1 and to Amended Cts 2-3.  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.  Court relies on the criminal complaint for a factual basis.  BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and approves the DPA on Ct 1 and finds defendant guilty on Cts 2-3.
Counsel make sentencing arguments.

BY THE COURT:  Ct 1:  DPA approved.

Cts 2-3:  Sentence withheld, defendant placed on probation for a period of 24 months, concurrent to each other, with the following conditions:  *Pay costs of $243.00, each count.  *Pay restitution for past due child support and arrears in the amount of $5,675.91.  *Pay current child support payments.  *Counseling as recommended by the agent.  *Maintain full-time employment or comply with work search orders in the child support case.
Preliminary hearing on July 24, 2014 at 02:00 pm.
